article.description: Rayjon Tucker scored 19 points and Florida Gulf Coast held off Kennesaw State for a 79-74 victory Thursday night for the Eagles' eighth straight victory.
article.headline: FGCU holds off Kennesaw State 79-74
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Rayjon Tucker scored 19 points and Florida Gulf Coast held off Kennesaw State for a 79-74 victory Thursday night for the Eagles' eighth straight victory. Christian Terrell added 16 points and Zach Johnson 15. Kennesaw State (5-15, 1/3 Atlantic Sun) was within six with 1:07 to go after a 3-pointer by Yonel Brown and got the ball back on a turnover. But Brown was called for a charge and Tucker added three free throws in the final 25 seconds. Tucker scored 12 points in the first half when FGCU (13-7, 4-0) took a 42-32 lead. The Eagles led by 14 early in the second half before the Owls got within four. Kendrick Ray scored a career-high 31 points for the Owls. Brown added 20. The Eagles had a 39-28 rebounding edge including 13-5 on the offensive glass, plus a 48-28 scoring advantage in the paint.
